      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://discoveroutdoors.com/lakes/peach-lake/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The lake itself stretches across Westchester and Putnam counties, making it a bi‑county waterway.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        16
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peach_Lake%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The Peach Lake community sits on the lake’s northeastern shore, overlooking the water.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peach_Lake%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "From the 1850s to 1915, the area thrived as a dairy hub, even hosting a Borden Condensed Milk plant in nearby Brewster.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peach_Lake%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "In 2019, Peach Lake became one of only two New York lakes to use alum to bind phosphorus into the sediment.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        25
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peach_Lake%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "By spring 2013, every one of the 484 homes and businesses around Peach Lake was connected to the new sewer system.",
